title: [Feature] OS Mode
body: OS Mode is a micro-kernel architecture within wasmrun that provides a complete operating system-like environment for running multi-language projects in a sandboxed WASM environment. Think of it as a lightweight OS running inside your browser that can execute Node.js, Python, Go, and other language projects. Currently, nodejs project support is under-development. This feature isn't complete yet. But ready to be opened up to everyone. Can use some thoughts from the community and hopefully build a much better interface than what's currently available. There's much work pending on this. But I'm confident this'll be of great importance and value as a devtool.
